            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Better separation of concerns and less risk of output generation logic bleeding into tree walking logic. And we can add new output formats without even looking at the tree walking logic. But maybe it's a weak reason that's just based on my initial impressions of `gen_help_html.lua`, where the two are (understandably) not completely separate. I'll experiment.\n\n(side note: this is not going very fast because I have very limited time to dedicate to it. But hey I'll keep chipping at it)",
