            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> but I don't get why it's better to walk a JSON tree vs walking a treesitter tree directly\n\nI originally proposed this because both Hugo and Typst can consume and build documents based on JSON, and both do a pretty good job in it because you're close to the actual document generation. It wouldn't involve string formatting html tags for example. ",
